    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169/3943: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-08T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 8, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>995. For Foreign Economic Administration. Reference Department’s circular airgram
                    May 25, 11:15 a.m.<note n="64" xml:id="d710fn64">Not printed; it conveyed a
                        proposal to require import recommendations only for commodities on a
                        positive list, effective July 1, 1944. The most important items listed were
                        steel, cotton, rubber, rayon, wood, and their products
                        (103.9169/3680a).</note> Country Agency has been consulted but must present
                    matter of further roll back to a minimum positive list to Board of Directors for
                    decision which is expected to be rendered about June 13. In the meantime,
                    Adriasola, manager of the Country Agency, has assured Embassy that he believes
                    the Country Agency will agree. As soon as possible after the definite <pb
                        facs="0759" n="745" xml:id="pg_745"/> decision of the Board, the Embassy
                    will inform the Department by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
